Our legitimate interest to advertise our products and services and provide more relevant advertising to you and our potential customers as well as to improve the relevance and effectiveness of our marketing efforts and enhance overall marketing performance.
We consider our Advertising Partners such as Meta and Google as jointly responsible with us (joint controllers) in these scenarios. We refer to their respective terms for further information of how they process personal data.
We have entered into an agreement with Meta regarding joint controllership in accordance with Article 26 of the GDPR and have determined who fulfils the applicable obligations under the GDPR for each phase of the processing. The joint controllership agreement can be accessed
here
.
To obtain statistical insights into our marketing communications.
Engagement metrics
Email open / click rates, details on your interactions with our emails and links clicked on. The emails and our website contain tracking pixels which measure the opening and click frequency.
Your use of our Volvo Cars App, including downloads, activations, license status, subscriptions, social media channel(s) reach, engagements, clicks, opens, leads, video playback based on IP´s, tracking pixels and third-party connectors.
Our legitimate interest in measuring the efficiency of our marketing communications and activities subject to, whenever obtaining information from a device, the user having accepted advertising cookies.
* This would be the case for app usage when you are logged in with your Volvo ID and in the case of web browsing, when you follow a link provided to you in an email and when you request a service linked to your phone number or email address, such as making a booking for a service or registering for a test drive.
