Article version 2025.28.0
Privacy Notice - CCTV video surveillance
Effective from:
2025-01-28
Published at:
2025-01-28
This document describes how Volvo Cars (as defined below) processes your personal data when using CCTV cameras for surveillance on and in connection to our premises (hereinafter “video surveillance”).
You can find below:
Who we are
;
What personal data we collect and why
;
How long we keep your data
;
Who we share your personal data with
;
Your rights in relation to the data processing we perform
;
Contact information
;
Updates to this notice
.
1. Who we are
The entity responsible for the processing of personal data in relation to the video surveillance is Volvo Car Corporation, having its registered office at Assar Gabrielssons väg, 405 31, Göteborg, Sweden, company registration number 556074-3089, hereinafter referred to as “
Volvo Cars
”, “
we
”, or “
us
”.
2. What personal data we collect and why
We process your personal data when we collect and use camera video surveillance images and video recordings for the purpose of safeguarding our property, business operations and the security of our personnel as well as the general public visiting our facilities. This processing is based on the legal ground of our legitimate interest (GDPR Art 6.1.f) where we made the assessment that our interest in processing the personal data in order to being able safeguard our property, business operations and the security of our personnel as well as the general public visiting our facilities outweighs the interests of the individual. If you would like more information on this assessment, please contact us.
3. How long we keep your data
The CCTV video recordings will be kept for a maximum of 30 days from the date of recording. In the case where we have reasons to believe that a crime has occurred, the recordings will be stored and used as long as is needed for the investigation to be finalized by law enforcement. When we are conducting internal policy breach investigations, then the recordings will be stored and used as long as is needed for the investigation and any external legal process to be completed and finalized.
After the end of the above provided retention times, the recordings will be deleted.
4. Who we share your personal data with
We will share your personal data with the following categories of third parties, on a need-to-know basis:
Our processors supporting our activity in general, such as providers of IT solutions;
Our processors supporting the delivery of the video surveillance, which are limited by contract in their ability to use your personal data for any purpose other than to provide services for us in compliance with each data processing agreement in place;
Law enforcement authorities (e.g. police, courts); Personal data needs to be shared or may be shared with law enforcement authorities (e.g., police, courts), to comply with a legal obligation, or our legitimate interest in providing data when a severe crime is suspected, or when it is necessary to establish, exercise or defend ourselves against legal claims.
5. Your rights in relation to the data processing we perform
You have specific legal rights granted by the General Data Protection Regulation relating to the personal data we process about you. You can withdraw your consent or object to our processing of your data, access the data we hold about you, ask for rectification or restriction of your data, request to have your data ported to another entity, request that we delete your data, and finally you can file a complaint with a data protection supervisory authority.
Details about your rights – what they mean, when and how you can exercise them - can be found in our
General Privacy Notice
.
6. Contact information
In order to exercise your rights and submit a data subject rights request,
please use this personal information privacy rights request form
. If you have any other questions regarding the subject matter of personal data protection, you can contact us at the following post address:
Data Protection Officer
Volvo Car Corporation
Post address: Assar Gabrielssons Väg, SE-405 31 Gothenburg, Sweden
Contact information of the Volvo Cars Corporation Data Protection Officer:
globdpo@volvocars.com
Any questions about this notice not related to personal data:
swedencr@volvocars.com
7. Updates to this notice
We continuously review our use of CCTV video surveillance solutions and we subsequently review and update this privacy notice as needed. The date at the top of this privacy notice lets you know when it was last updated. We will handle your personal data in a manner consistent with this privacy notice under which it was collected unless we have your consent to handle it differently.
